    <abstract id="aspace_a66b610eda02c404e221c5af95f9d4c8">Joan Roelofs was Professor of Political Science at Keene State College from 1979 until 2012 specializing in green public adminsitration, the political power of foundations and the ideas of pre-Marxist socialist Charles Fourier. She is the author of <title render="italic">Greening Cities: Building Just</title>, <title render="italic">Sustainable Communities</title>, and <title render="italic">Foundations and Public Policy</title>. She is also a practitioner of book arts. This collection consists of various papers, articles, notes and fliers regarding the environment, labor issues and the socio-political situation in America during the late-20th century; as well as issues of numerous publications examining contemporary issues in climate change, environmental politics, and energy policy and development.</abstract>
    <langmaterial id="aspace_e33ff1f96944b1132b2e10455b504d19">Materials are in English.</langmaterial>
